The paper focuses on using deep neural networks for personalized fashion recommendation, which involves image processing (extracting features from clothing items), machine learning (matching user preferences with clothing items), and information retrieval (retrieving relevant clothing items from a large dataset). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques such as fine-tuning and multi-layer fully-connected networks, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper deals with a large-scale dataset and social network analysis, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
